                                                                        "title": "FedEx St. Jude Classic",
                                                                        "body": "Became the fourth player in the 60-year history of the FedEx St. Jude Classic to successfully defend their title and just the second since the event moved to TPC Southwind in 1989. Started the final round three shots back and posted one of two bogey-free rounds on Sunday, a 66, to win his second PGA TOUR title in his 74th career start at the age of 24 years, 2 months, 4 days. Became the third player to successfully defend a title in the 2016-17 PGA TOUR Season (behind Justin Thomas/CIMB Classic and Hideki Matsuyama/Waste Management Phoenix Open). Moved to 10th in the FedEx Cup standings and No. 5 in the Presidents Cup U.S. Team standings."
