                                                                                "tournamentId": "R2022010",
                                                                                "title": "The Honda Classic",
                                                                                "body": "Held a five-stroke lead entering the final round of The Honda Classic before finishing solo-fourth, his third top-10 in seven starts at the event. Became the first player on TOUR since Dustin Johnson at the 2017 WGC-HSBC Champions (6) to lead by five or more strokes through 54 holes, compete in the final round and fail to convert to victory. Also held the lead after the second round."
