                                                                                "tournamentId": "",
                                                                                "title": "",
                                                                                "body": "Advanced to the FedExCup Playoffs for the fourth time in as many attempts on TOUR. With only one top-10 (at the U.S. Open), marked his first season on the PGA TOUR he failed to record multiple top-10s. Made 18 cuts in 23 starts while dealing with a wrist injury which caused him to end his season at No. 70 in the FedExCup."
                                                                            },
                                                                            {
                                                                                "year": 2018,
                                                                                "tournamentId": "R2018026",
                                                                                "title": "U.S. Open",
                                                                                "body": "Entering the final round of the U.S. Open tied for the lead and in the final pairing, posted a 73 to finish T6, his first top-10 in a major. Began the third round 11 strokes behind leader Dustin Johnson and shot a third-round 4-under 66, one of just three sub-70 rounds on Saturday. Marked his 100th PGA TOUR start and fourth in the U.S. Open."
